The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | Govt funds MIT boy 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Govt funds MIT boy 
          A STAFF REPORTER                            The Telegraph report on May 6 about Panda                                   
	Calcutta, May 16: The Bengal government has promised to fund the transit expenses of a 17-year-old village boy who had earned a full scholarship to the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.        
	A higher secondary examinee from Bankura Zilla School, Anshuman Panda has never had a TV at home: his father Bidhan Chandra Panda earns Rs 3,500 a month.        
	The chief minister has personally taken interest, and we have decided to do everything necessary to facilitate the boys entry into the coveted institution, finance minister Asim Dasgupta said.        
	Dasgupta, an MIT alumnus himself, said the state would pay Rs 2.25 lakh for expenses.                                                                                                                                            
